{
  "stem": "10181.4",
  "chunk_idx": 14,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "After about nine months, they-- I can give you the exact date when we left.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was January 11, 1944.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was after nine months in Westerbork, and there were very few people left in the orphanage.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We were called to go on a train to Bergen-Belsen.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now, we were the first train from Westerbork to Bergen-Belsen.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And why we were-- why we were-- why we were sent to Bergen-Belsen?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was a very simple.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "On that same train, the majority of people on it were certificate-- what we called certificate Jews.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "What were certificate Jews?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "These were young people, you know, young, I mean, 18 and older, but not-- not very old, who had been on farms, on [NON-ENGLISH] in Holland, preparing to go on [NON-ENGLISH], to go to Israel-- to Palestine, not to Israel.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they had gotten certificates from the British to immigrate.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You know, the immigration to Palestine was very restricted, but they had got certificates to immigrate to Palestine, valid certificates.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But they got them too late.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They-- they couldn't get to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So some of those certificate Jews were kept by the Germans in Westerbork because the-- the Germans obviously liked, you know, they very much respected official papers.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This was a very official paper, and they were kept there maybe for exchange, to exchange them for-- for Germans, whatever.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we were sent with them because our-- I don't know why we were sent with them, but we were supposed to also to be a foreign-- British nationality.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We didn't have really any papers, but that's what it was.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I remember them well because we were-- at the time on that train, there were very few children.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't know why.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Later on, families came.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
